Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is the bias-variance tradeoff?
AI Response

High bias = underfitting (oversimplified model); high variance = overfitting (over-complex model). Good
models balance both to minimize total prediction error.

Example 1.2

User

What is data augmentation?
AI Response

Data augmentation artificially increases training data by applying transformations like rotation, cropping, and
flipping to existing samples, improving model generalization.

Example 1.3

User

What is the softmax function?
AI Response

Softmax converts a vector of raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1, typically used as the final
activation in multi-class classification models.

Example 1.4

User

What is precision vs recall?
AI Response

Precision is correct positive predictions / all positive predictions. Recall is correct positive predictions / all
actual positives. F1 score harmonically balances both.

Example 1.5

User

What is backpropagation?
AI Response

Backpropagation computes gradients of the loss with respect to each weight by applying the chain rule
backwards through the network, enabling weight updates via gradient descent.

Example 1.6

User

What is transfer learning?
AI Response

Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.

Example 1.7

User

What is BERT?
AI Response



BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) is a pre-trained transformer model that
understands context from both directions in a sentence, excelling at NLP classification tasks.

Example 1.8

User

What is gradient descent?
AI Response

Gradient descent is an optimization algorithm that iteratively adjusts model parameters in the direction
opposite to the gradient of the loss function to find a minimum.

Example 1.9

User

What is overfitting?
AI Response

Overfitting occurs when a model learns training data too well—including noise—causing poor generalization
to new data. Symptoms include high train accuracy but low validation accuracy.

Example 1.10

User

What is attention mechanism?
AI Response

Attention allows a model to focus on relevant input parts during output generation. Self-attention in
transformers computes weighted relationships between all token pairs.



